Peru Stocks: Atacocha, Pomalca, Relapasa, Siderperu, Volcan

-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 
2011-04-13T20:46:02Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-13/peru-stocks-atacocha-pomalca-relapasa-siderperu-volcan.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses
and share prices are as of 4:10 p.m.  New York  time.  The Lima General Index fell for a third session, dropping
6.2 percent to 18,613.96 for the biggest one-day decline since
November 2008. The MSCI All Peru Capped Index declined 4.2
percent to 2,569.07.  Industrial stocks slumped on investor concern opposition
candidate Ollanta Humala will win the presidential runoff vote
in June and expand government control of the economy, said
Hernando Pastor, an analyst at Lima-based Juan Magot y Asociados
SAB.  Refineria la Pampilla SA (RELAPAC1 PE), a unit of  Spain ’s
Repsol YPF SA, plunged 13 percent to 1.43 soles. Empresa
Agroindustrial Pomalca SA (POMALCC1 PE), a unit of Grupo Oviedo,
fell 13 percent to 42 centimos, a two-year low, after sugar
declined in New York.  Empresa Siderurgica del Peru SAA (SIDERC1)  (SIDERC1
PE), a unit of Gerdau SA, Latin America’s largest steelmaker,
dropped 13 percent to 1.24 soles. Corp. Aceros Arequipa SA
(CORAREI1 PE), the Lima-based steelmaker, fell for a fifth
session, losing 11 percent to 2.44 soles.  Copper and zinc miners dropped after metals declined in New
York and  London .  Alturas Minerals Corp. (ALT)  , a Canadian copper and gold
exploration company, plummeted 20 percent to 12 cents. Cia.
Minera Atacocha SA (ATACOBC1 PE), the Lima-based zinc and lead
producer, dropped 14 percent to 93 centimos, a two-year low.
Volcan Cia Minera SAA (VOLCABC1 PE), Peru’s largest zinc and
silver producer, fell 10 percent to 3.23 soles.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Alex Emery  in  Lima  at 
 aemery1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
 papadopoulos@bloomberg.net  